The management of the Transmission Company of Nigeria (TCN) said it has trained its staff members and presented outstanding performance certificates to 11 engineers. The Engineers’ Development Programme – Module 1 training was held in Osogbo, Osun State recently. The Managing Director of TCN, Mr. Usman Gur Mohammed presented the certificates to the outstanding engineers at the TCN headquarters in Abuja, a statement said. Mr Mohammed who was represented by the Head, Independent System Operator (ISO), Engr. Mamman Lawal said the management is encouraged to train more staff, adding that the engineers were now part of pacesetters of high standards within their departments. Speaking for the awardees, Mr. Ibrahim Aliyu said they will not relent in practising what they have learnt. He also appealed to the management to extend such intensive trainings the staff in other departments in order to have an efficient transmission company. At least 308 newly recruited engineers, divided into five batches, in Independent System Operator Sub-sector were trained under the programme. Some of courses include, Switch Gear Application, System Communication, Fundamentals of Power System Control as well as SCADA/EMS, Power System Network Configuration and Safety on Outage Management Procedures. TCN to split, eyes $5m digital power transmission control rooms TCN to split, eyes N1.8bn digital power control rooms TCN loses N3.6bn transformers, blames DisCos’ poor networks Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.